							<Experience
								dates="March 2020 - Present"
								role="VP of Product Design"
								body="<ul class='list-disc pl-5'><li class='mb-8 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Managed a cross-functional team of 3 designers and 3 front-end engineers, overseeing design projects with a third-party agency as VP of Product Design. Led the migration from a static Django website to Webflow for marketing pages and implemented Vue mini-apps for other pages, enhancing site interactivity by 40%.</li><li class='mb-8 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Conducted A/B testing using Google Optimize; utilized Google Tag Manager, Google Analytics, Amplitude, and Posthog for comprehensive data collection and analysis; implemented data-driven improvements that boosted conversion rates by 25%.</li><li class='mb-8 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Led the ideation, design, and front-end development for 2 native iOS apps, fostering creativity through weekly design sprints with techniques such as mapping, competitor audits, and brainstorming. Introduced Lean UX principles and leveraged Figma and FigJam for seamless design collaboration.</li><li class='mb-8 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Orchestrated Boombox acquisition, managing design and tech hand-off, refactoring Nuxt codebase, addressing 50+ bugs, improving performance by 30%, and initiating cost-saving measures, reducing expenses by 20%.</li><li class='mb-0 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Facilitated in migrating the company from a number of PM tools to ClickUp, streamlining project management processes and improving team efficiency by 25%. Collaborated with the marketing team to map email life-cycles and run high-performing Optinmonster campaigns, increasing lead generation by 40%.</li></ul>"
							/>
							<Experience
								dates="December 2019 - March 2020"
								role="Product Design Consultant"
								body="<ul class='list-disc pl-5'><li class='mb-0 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Transformed Droplr’s online presence by developing a custom WordPress multi-site theme; emphasized SEO and page speed, resulting in a 115% rise in organic traffic and a 99/85 Google PageSpeed score.</li><li class='mb-8 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Led an initiative to standardize, improve, and codify the use of brand assets across the company, ensuring brand consistency and enhancing overall visual identity.</li></ul>"
							/>
							<Experience
								dates="March 2014 - March 2020"
								role="Sr. Manager, UX/UI & Frontend Development at Peterson's"
								body="<ul class='list-disc pl-5'><li class='mb-8 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Led UX/UI and front-end development efforts as a senior manager, managing small teams and executing product visions from wireframing and high-fidelity mock-ups to prototyping and production-ready code within an Agile environment.</li><li class='mb-8 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Spearheaded a 6-month project to migrate Peterson's from a 15-year-old .NET stack to modern technologies including Bootstrap, Laravel, VueJS, Auth0, AWS, Docker/Vagrant, Yarn, and Git/GitLab, resulting in a 40% improvement in site performance and a 50% reduction in maintenance costs.</li><li class='mb-8 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Designed and developed a complex native mobile app with an international team in 3 months. App secured App Store feature within the first week, garnered a 4.6-star rating, and achieved 10,000 downloads in the initial 3 months.</li><li class='mb-0 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Attained Certified Scrum Master (CSM) certification from Scrum Alliance, enabling the implementation of agile methodologies that accelerated project completion timelines.</li></ul>"
							/>
							<Experience
								dates="July 2017 - December 2019"
								role="Freelance Design & Development at ETHDenver"
								body="<ul class='list-disc pl-5'><li class='mb-0 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Directed ETHDenver's web enhancement, merging WordPress and Devfolio to streamline promotional sites, forms with Advanced Custom Fields, schedules with Vue mini-apps, and social media; achieved a 96% CSAT score for event applications with improved UX.</li></ul>"
							/>
							<Experience
								dates="January 2014 - August 2017"
								role="Freelance Design & Development at Inspirato"
								body="<ul class='list-disc pl-5'><li class='mb-8 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Designed and developed the WordPress blog for Inspirato, enhancing user engagement by 40% and elevating the brand's digital presence in the luxury hospitality market.</li><li class='mb-0 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Engineered and launched the 'Inspirato with American Express' partnership, optimizing the user experience for card-members and driving a 40% increase in membership sign-ups within the first quarter.</li></ul>"
							/>
							<Experience
								dates="December 2011 - March 2014"
								role="Sr. WordPress Designer/Developer at Webolutions"
								body="<ul class='list-disc pl-5'><li class='mb-8 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Won two Communicator Awards: Award of Excellence in the Food & Beverage category for PotatoesUSA, and Award of Visual Appeal for Fossil Trace Golf Club, highlighting exceptional design and development skills.</li><li class='mb-8 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Designed and developed all client websites with a focus on user-centered design principles, best practices, and industry trends, ensuring high-quality and impactful web solutions.</li><li class='mb-0 opacity-75 text-base leading-relaxed'>Independently delivered new websites on a weekly basis, consistently meeting tight deadlines and maintaining high quality standards.</li></ul>"
							/>
							<Experience
